<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>

<title>TURN</title>
</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I turn a specified number of degrees.</i> </h3>

	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	</p>
	<p><b>TURN</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for columns: 69 rotation-angle 10                                                         
turn-right rotation-angle
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>You can change the contents of the text area to another number or the value of a parameter (see <a href="DEFINE-PARAMETER.html">
	DEFINE-PARAMETER</a>). Using a negative value will turn 
	left instead.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>

	<p>

	<a href="TURN-REPEATEDLY.html">TURN-REPEATEDLY</a> repeatedly turns.
	<a title="TURN-RANDOMLY" href="TURN-RANDOMLY.html">

	TURN-RANDOMLY</a> turns back and forth a random amount.</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>This uses <b>turn-right</b>, a BehaviourComposer NetLogo command.</p>

	<h2>History</h2>

	<p><a href="TURN.html">TURN</a> was implemented by Ken Kahn.</p>
</body>
</html>
